  "unlimited": {
    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "What do you mean by unlimited agents?",
        "answer": "For all the 'Unlimited Agents' plans, you can add any number of staff in your corporate domain. For example, if happyfox.com is your email domain, anyone with that email address can be invited as an agent."
      },
      {
        "question": "What are custom fields and how does the limit work?",
        "answer": "Custom fields are additional custom properties that you can add to a ticket, contact or contact group. Unlimited Agents plans have custom field limits. Ticket fields, contact fields, and contact-group fields collectively make up for the total custom fields used on your account."
      },
      {
        "question": "What happens once we reach the total ticket limit?",
        "answer": "You will be billed for every 5,000 additional tickets depending on your plan. The total ticket limit only applies to 'Unlimited Agents' plans."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I delete tickets to limit the total ticket count?",
        "answer": "Yes, you can delete tickets to stay below the total ticket count. However, please note that deleted tickets cannot be restored. Consider upgrading to a higher plan if you need to retain all ticket history."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I pay month-on-month for 'Unlimited Agents' plans?",
        "answer": "No. Unfortunately, we don't have a month-on-month option for 'Unlimited Agents' plans."
      },
      {
        "question": "What are the available billing cycles?",
        "answer": "For unlimited agent plans, we offer annual and 2-year savings plan (paid upfront) options."
      }
    ],
